A common student error is to always return inside a loop body, which causes the loop to only ever excute once:

```python
def all_pos(lst):
    for num in lst:
       if num > 0:
           return True
       else:
           return False
```

pylint will pick up on the return True/return False simplification (ask @shweta97 for details), but it won't pick up on the fact that the loop only runs once. We should really check this, as it happens all the time!
